# Download Lubuntu-32-bit-with-Pre-Installed-Hadoop from here:

https://mega.nz/#!J4lEkSQC!iAx-H0m0-OmW0u_mDGdY2ICJmqawQZsmRQAPf0B6Qls

Unzip it.

# Download VMware Workstation Player 
https://www.vmware.com/products/workstation-player.html

https://my.vmware.com/en/web/vmware/free#desktop_end_user_computing/vmware_workstation_player/14_0

The Workstation Player is free for non-comercial Use.

Open the player , select open an existing VM

Go to the folder of extract and select the only .vmx File

# Before you start edit the VM

Remove Printer
Allocate the amount of memory you need. I have given it 4GB because in 32bit guest you cannot exceed over 4GB
Edit the address in the Hard Disk
Remove CD Drive

# Install VMware Tools and Drivers.

